  "prompt": "How do I ask a professor to take me as a PhD student after introductory talk?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to follow up after an initial discussion:\n\n1. Send a follow-up email promptly (within 1-2 days)\n- Thank them for their time\n- Reiterate your interest in their research\n- Briefly highlight how your background/skills align with their work\n- Ask about potential next steps\n\n2. Include in the email:\n- A concise summary of your research interests\n- Your relevant academic/research experience\n- Why you're specifically interested in their research group\n- Your academic credentials (GPA, publications, etc.)\n- Attach your current CV/resume\n\n3. Be professional and specific:\n- Demonstrate you've thoroughly researched their work\n- Show genuine enthusiasm\n- Be clear about your goals\n- Request a follow-up meeting or discussion\n\n4. Practical suggestions:\n- Reference specific details from your initial conversation\n- Be clear but not pushy\n- Express openness to their guidance\n- Offer to provide additional information\n\n5. Follow-up strategy:\n- If no response after 1 week, send a polite reminder\n- Be patient and respectful\n- Consider alternative potential supervisors if needed\n\n6. Prepare additional materials:\n- Research proposal draft\n- Letters of recommendation\n- Writing samples/publications\n\nRemember: Persistence and professionalism are key.",
